          "type": "struct",
          "name": "speed",
          "definition": "wind_scalar_function_struct"
        },
        {
          "type": "explanation",
          "name": "DECORATOR WIND MOTION",
          "definition": "These are all a function of the wind speed (between 0 MPH on the left and 200 MPH on the right)\n\nbend: how much the decorators bend - 0.0 is standing straight up, 10.0 is super-flattened\noscillation: how much the decorators 'oscillate' at a given speed\nfrequency: how fast the oscillation waves each decorator\ngust size: big gusts move large areas of decorators in sync.  small gusts give more variation\n"
        },
        {
          "type": "struct",
          "name": "bend",
          "definition": "wind_scalar_function_struct"
        },
